You have the authentication Manger which calls to authentication provider which talks to the UserDetailsService.
So the User Details service has one method which gets the user information based on the user information.Spring security has a way
for you to provide this userdetails service. And it will take the user name and will return your user object type of userdetails.
Any time if you wants to look up for a user userDetailsService can be called. And Spring security will manage the rest. It will show the
login form and get the user name and password. And when it need to validate the user information its going to call 

